name: Armor Cross Ring
description:
This shield ring, etched with a cross design and adorned with a 5mm green aventurine stone settled in fine silver, is one of a kind. The length of the armor is 1 3/4". I have oxidized its surface to pop its design and I have sealed it with a thin layer of varnish to protect it. The back was closed with a sterling silver band and adorned with sterling silver beads and tubes.
It fits a finger sized 7.25 to 8.25.
The green aventurine is a stone that can be placed on any part of the body and dissolves negative energies and obstacles.
The cross is a symbol of faith.

name: Rustic Mixed Metal Cross Necklace
description:
This rustic cross was made in etched copper and sterling silver. The sterling silver cross holds a 5mm green aventurine stone. Joining the cross I have added a cornaline bead wrapped in sterling silver, a sterling silver charm with the word “paz” stamped on it (paz means peace), a sterling silver spring and a green leather cord adorned with sterling beads. The pendant, including the textured silver link, is 7 cm / 2 ¾” and hangs from a 16” caramel leather cord. Closure is a sterling silver and copper clasp. The whole piece was blackened for an aged time look. A protective varnish was given to seal the piece.
The green aventurine is a stone that can be placed on any part of the body, being especially effective on the solar plexus and dissolves negative energies and obstacles.The cornaline is a stone that helps connect us and open our Sacral Chakra, which governs sexuality, emotions, passion and creativity. The cross is a symbol of faith.
